    DESCRIPTION:
      'This includes the English &amp;ldquo;West Country&amp;rdquo; plus ciders inspired by that style. These ciders are made with bittersweet and bitter-sharp apple varieties cultivated specifically for cider making. Generally dry, full-bodied, austere. Entrants MUST specify carbonation level (still or petillant). Entrants MUST specify sweetness (dry to medium). Entrants MAY specify variety of apple for a single varietal cider; if specified, varietal character will be expected.',
